step_data.thought:
I've now explored all four main map layers available in OpenStreetMap for New York City:

1. Standard - The default OpenStreetMap style
2. CyclOSM - Focused on cycling routes and infrastructure
3. ÖPNVKarte - Focused on public transportation networks
4. Humanitarian - Designed for humanitarian response with clearer visibility of infrastructure

I've also explored the overlay options:
- Map Notes - This appears to be already enabled (clicking on it didn't change its state as it was already checked)
- Map Data - This is currently disabled and can't be toggled
- Public GPS Traces - This shows GPS traces that users have uploaded to OpenStreetMap

I've successfully completed the exploration of different map layers available in OpenStreetMap for New York City. I should now summarize my findings to the user.
step_data.action: stop('I have explored the different map layers available in OpenStreetMap for New York City. There are four main base map styles: (1) Standard - the default OpenStreetMap style, (2) CyclOSM - optimized for cycling routes and infrastructure, (3) ÖPNVKarte - focused on public transportation networks, and (4) Humanitarian - designed for humanitarian response with clearer visibility of infrastructure. Additionally, there are overlay options including Map Notes and Public GPS Traces that can be enabled to show additional information on top of the base maps.')
